cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper is about scheduling VMs in a distributed server platform, which is a core topic in distributed computing. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper deals with resource allocation and scheduling, which are important topics in control systems. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper is motivated by cloud computing applications, which heavily rely on networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes a scheduling algorithm and discusses its computational complexity. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed algorithm through extensive simulations.
